Soak your @wooden skewers{4} in water until you need them, to stop them burning
in the oven. Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Remove the core from your @red pepper{1} and chop into roughly 3cm pieces.
Chop your @British chicken thighs{4} into 3cm pieces too. Put your pepper and
chicken in a #bowl{}. Mix together your @rice vinegar{1}, @soy sauce{1.5},
@Muscovado sugar{1} and @chilli ketchup{1} along with 1 tsp of water. Add this
to the chicken and pepper, mix around so they have a good coating and leave to
the side.

Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil. Peel and finely chop your @ginger{1}(peeled
and finely chopped).

> You can peel your ginger with the back of a spoon!

Peel and chop your @garlic clove{1}(peeled and chopped). Finely slice your
@spring onions{3}(finely sliced), separating chopped green tops and white bits.

Thread your chicken and pepper pieces onto the wooden skewers, alternating
chicken and red pepper (if you don't have exactly the right ratio of chicken to
pepper pieces it doesn't matter!). Then put the skewers on a #baking tray{}.
Put them in the oven to cook for ~{15%minutes}, turn them over halfway through
cooking.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add your @egg noodle nest{2} to the boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes} or
until cooked. Then drain and submerge in cold water to prevent them cooking
any further.

> We will stir-fry these later.

In the meantime, you need to make your carrots into ribbons: pull a
#vegetable peeler{} lengthways along the @carrot{2}. This will make lovely thin
ribbons (if you use a knife they will be too thick).

Add 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp} to a large #frying pan{}, add your ginger, garlic and
whites of your spring onions to the pan and cook for ~{3%minutes} before adding
your carrot ribbons. Stir-fry for another ~{4%minutes} before adding any leftover
soy mixture. Toss everything together then drain your noodles and add them to
the pan, stir-fry for another couple of mins. Make sure everything is well
combined, then serve in bowls with your skewers on top and some @lime{1/2}(cut
into wedges) wedges on the side to squeeze over. Sprinkle the greens of your
spring onion and enjoy!